An Example:^^The specific virtue of a well-designed microworld is in permitting the uncluttered presentation of a powerful idea.  The isolation and stepping of a single variable is a heuristic applied across the entire range of scientific thought.  We have introduced children to this powerful idea with the POLYSPI procedure (For more detail about this example, see Lawler, l980):
