Are there powerful ideas in language as there are in mathematics ?  If so, are they sufficiently separable to be crisply captured in engaging applications ?  We believe these are research questions which can be addressed with the word worlds machine.  How should language be "reconceptualized" for young children ?  We now try to sketch a concrete answer to that question by exploring four aspects of a young child's use of the word worlds system.
